<section id="fs-id2684549">
<title>Flow and Resistance as Causes of Pressure Drops</title>
    <para id="import-auto-id2671388">You may have noticed that water pressure in your home might be lower than normal on hot summer days when there is more use. This pressure drop occurs in the water main before it reaches your home. Let us consider flow through the water main as illustrated in <link target-id="import-auto-id3191604"/>. We can understand why the pressure <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:msub><m:mi>P</m:mi><m:mrow><m:mn>1</m:mn></m:mrow></m:msub></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow></m:math> to the home drops during times of heavy use by rearranging</para>
    <equation id="import-auto-id3230032">
