<m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mn>0.5</m:mn><m:mspace width="0.25em"/><m:msup><m:mtext>cm</m:mtext><m:mrow><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:mrow></m:msup></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math>, with a total of

<m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mtext>10</m:mtext><m:mspace width="0.25em"/><m:msup><m:mtext>cm</m:mtext><m:mrow><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:mrow></m:msup></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math>. In that manner, the resistance of the branchings is reduced so that pressure is not entirely lost. Moreover, because

<m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow>
