</m:math> increases through branching, the average velocity of the blood in the smaller vessels is reduced. The blood velocity in the aorta (<m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mtext>diameter</m:mtext><m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo><m:mn>1</m:mn></m:mrow><m:mspace width="0.25em"/><m:mtext>cm</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math>) is about 25 cm/s, while in the capillaries (<m:math>
 
