</m:math> in diameter) the velocity is about 1 mm/s. This reduced velocity allows the blood to exchange substances with the cells in the capillaries and alveoli in particular.</para></section>

<section id="fs-id1336364" class="section-summary"><title>Section Summary</title><list id="fs-id1395110"><item id="import-auto-id1997134">Laminar flow is characterized by smooth flow of the fluid in layers that do not mix.</item>
