    <item id="import-auto-id2653755">Flow is proportional to pressure difference and inversely proportional to resistance:
    <equation id="eip-472"><m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi>Q</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo><m:mfrac><m:mrow><m:msub><m:mi>P</m:mi><m:mrow><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:mrow></m:msub><m:mo stretchy="false">−</m:mo><m:msub><m:mi>P</m:mi><m:mrow><m:mn>1</m:mn></m:mrow></m:msub></m:mrow><m:mi>R</m:mi></m:mfrac></m:mrow></m:mrow><m:mrow/><m:mo>.</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math></equation></item>
    <item id="import-auto-id1936008">For laminar flow in a tube, Poiseuille’s law for resistance states that
    <equation id="eip-18"><m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi>R</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo><m:mfrac><m:mrow><m:mn>8</m:mn><m:mi>η</m:mi><m:mi>l</m:mi></m:mrow><m:msup><m:mi fontstyle="italic">πr</m:mi><m:mrow><m:mn>4</m:mn></m:mrow></m:msup></m:mfrac></m:mrow></m:mrow><m:mrow/><m:mo>.</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math></equation></item>
