    <exercise id="fs-id2442683" type="problems-exercises">
<problem id="fs-id2452711">
 <para id="import-auto-id1577562">When physicians diagnose arterial blockages, they quote the reduction in flow rate. If the flow rate in an artery has been reduced to 10.0% of its normal value by a blood clot and the average pressure difference has increased by 20.0%, by what factor has the clot reduced the radius of the artery?</para>
