<problem id="fs-id3418450">
 <para id="import-auto-id1999971">During a marathon race, a runner’s blood flow increases to 10.0 times her resting rate. Her blood’s viscosity has dropped to 95.0% of its normal value, and the blood pressure difference across the circulatory system has increased by 50.0%. By what factor has the average radii of her blood vessels increased?</para>
    </problem>
<solution id="fs-id3008926">
    <para id="import-auto-id1575376">1.59</para></solution>
